            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Thursday, 13th Heshvan (October), 1852</date>.</p>
            <p>My friend and the object of my thoughts, ever before me:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“Whoever oppresses <placeName>Israel</placeName> rises to
                leadership”*. I, oppressed<lb/> man, have had to submit to the most despicable
                cabal. My friends should<lb/> at least have spared me the shameful pains as I have
                urgently begged<lb/> them to, and such as the relations of a Talmud
                    Haham<add>?</add> justify, and not<lb/> permit the thing to come to such a pass
                or decision. I urgently re-<lb/>quested of <persName>Wolf</persName> and his partner
                to make sure of the votes before a meet-<lb/>ing took place. I am very much
                disgusted and the thing <sic>may?</sic> God forbid,<lb/> spoil another position for
                me. There is no fear of God in this place.<lb/> Since my return, I suffer very much.
                I am under spiritual and bodily<lb/> stress. I do not know what to begin. I should
                like to pronounce my his-<lb/>tory on the basis or subscriptions. What shall I do,
                “A millstone is<lb/> around my neck”*. In my case , anyone has a chance to “Obtain
                entrance to<lb/> Paradise in one hour.”*</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I expect with certainty that in the <date>November</date> issue you
                will<lb/> continue my discussion. In fact, everything that you have in your
                posses-<lb/>sion. I am depending upon it, and also that you will correct the
                mistakes<lb/> which occurred in the <date>October</date> issue. I must urgently ask
                you to send me<lb/> the proof sheets by return post. I must have them to look them
                over.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Unfortunately, my <sic>heard</sic> is full, otherwise I would have
                sent<lb/> you for publication in the <date>December</date> issue, the plan for my
                history.<lb/> It consists of preface, general introduction, etc., I am very anxious
                to<lb/> see all this translated into English by you. With some of it you will<lb/>
                probably not be in agreement, but the thing must be properly understood.<lb/> I
                offer a public sanctification of God's name by breaking the neck of the<lb/>
                individual critics, such as <persName>Wise</persName>, and other rascals and by
                setting right<lb/> the better ones, such as <persName>Josh<add>?</add></persName>
                and <persName>Herzfeld</persName>. I think I shall send you part<lb/> of it
                tomorrow. What difference does it make if the “Occident” appears a<lb/> few days
                later? It will interest people of this land and others, especi-</p>
            <p>* Talmudic diction<add>?</add></p>
            <p>* Talmudic</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>ally if it is printed in German and English, but at the same time. But,<lb/> in any
                event, I must have the manuscript back. Please indicate to me<lb/> what you do not
                understand or cannot read. In case you cannot include<lb/> in the
                    <date>December</date> issue I must have the manuscript back, but you can<lb/>
                print the German in English characters.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If only I could get well and raise my spirits.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With heartfelt respect,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Sincerely yours,</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
